<subSubSection pageId="216" pageNumber="821" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="216.[709,1306,1314,1742]" pageId="216" pageNumber="821">
Recent phylogenetic research has placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[711,879,1476,1505]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Niviventer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="216" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="andersoni">N. andersoni</taxonomicName>
as sister to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1055,1200,1476,1505]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Niviventer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="216" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="excelsior">N. excelsior</taxonomicName>
. Specimens of N. excelsiorhave variously clustered within populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[1019,1182,1551,1585]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Niviventer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="216" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="andersoni">N. andersoni</taxonomicName>
, but this may be due to misidentification. Nwiventer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[713,836,1629,1663]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Niviventer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="216" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="andersoni">andersoni</taxonomicName>
is most likely a species complex, with three recognizable clades in north- eastern Sichuan, south-western Sichuan,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="216.[98,1306,1749,3279]" pageId="216" pageNumber="821">and Yunnan and south-eastern Tibet. Lu Liang and colleagues in 2015 recognized three subspecies, two of which were described based on cranial and pelage variation. There are no genetic data to validate these subspecies, but there is certainly genetic variation in the species that needs to be investigated. Three subspecies recognized.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="216" pageNumber="821" type="multiple">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="216" pageNumber="821" startId="216.[99,253,1911,1940]" targetBox="[95,685,1326,1739]" targetPageId="216">
